The paper discusses a new class of neural models for machine learning tasks, which combines the strengths of neural networks and Gaussian processes. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is focused on the development and analysis of algorithms that can learn from and make predictions on data. 

The paper also mentions applications in regression, optimization, and computer vision, which suggests that it could also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). 

Finally, the paper discusses the probabilistic nature of the model and its ability to estimate uncertainty, which could make it relevant to the sub-category cs.SY (Systems and Control), which deals with the analysis and design of systems that incorporate uncertainty and variability.
